text: Youn Hyun-jung (born 14 March 1979) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in heavyweight at the 2003 World Taekwondo Championships in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, by defeating Chen Zhong in the semifinal, and Nataša Vezmar in the final. She won a silver medal at the 2002 Asian Games, after being defeated by Wang I-hsien in the final. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in taekwondo Category:Medalists at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Asian Games silver medalists for South Korea Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
